A 52-year-old widow in Budalang'i constituency, Busia county, has lost 32 bags of rice valued at Sh120,000 when her grass thatched house was burnt to ashes in a suspected arson attack. Susan Ajwang said she had gone to relative's home in the neighbourhood on Friday night when her house caught fire. Efforts by neighbours to put out the fire were unsuccessful. She said she the rice and three bicycles. The family is appealing for help from well-wishers to enable them build another house. They are staying at a Good Samaritan's house. The incident has been reported to area assistant chief Augustine Dienya.      